      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, an exceptional example of 90s JDM engineering. This vehicle retains its numbers-matching 13B-REW rotary engine, featuring the factory-spec sequential twin-turbocharger arrangement that provides a linear power band and crisp throttle response. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by a lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent compression testing confirms optimal health across all rotor faces, with no evidence of seal degradation. Finished in its original paint with a flawless interior, this FD represents a rare opportunity to own a turnkey survivor with perfect mechanical synchronization and zero aftermarket interference.",
